content: The AI model is back on track after the bug fix. We've improved our testing protocols to avoid future issues. Moving forward with caution.
Just spoke at a local tech conference about AI ethics. The audience was receptive, and I've got several speaking invites for the next few months.
Revisited our integration failures from last month. We're now applying these learnings to our current blockchain development. Learning from mistakes.
Investors have requested another demo, this time focusing on the blockchain's security measures. Time to showcase our quantum-resistant algorithms.
Our quantum-resistant algorithm is now integrated. It's been a long haul, but this milestone feels like a victory for our team's dedication.
Preparing for a keynote on AI-driven finance at a fintech summit. This could solidify my position as a thought leader in ethical tech.
Had a heart-to-heart with my co-founder about our vision. We're more aligned than ever, ready to tackle the next investor meeting with full force.
Just got word that one of our potential investors wants to meet with our legal team to discuss partnership terms. This is getting real.
Our AI model is now at 20% better accuracy. This improvement could be the tipping point for our funding round. Optimism is high.
